.Dd April 6, 2001
.Dt GETBOOTFILE 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm getbootfile
.Nd get the name of the booted kernel file
.Sh LIBRARY
.Lb libutil
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In util.h
.Ft const char *
.Fn getbootfile void
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Fn getbootfile
returns a static pointer to the full path name of the file from which
the current kernel was loaded.
If it can not be determined, or the file is not ``secure'' (see
.Xr secure_path 3 ) ,
.Dv _PATH_UNIX
from
.Aq Pa paths.h
is returned instead.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr secure_path 3 ,
.Xr sysctl 3
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
function call appeared in
.Fx 2.0
and
.Nx 1.6 .
